The expression in the image is a simple algebraic equation involving the variables $x$ and $y$. It can be written in LaTeX format as follows:

$$
\begin{aligned}
x^2+y^2 & =3^2 \\
x^2+y^2 & =9 \\
x^2 & =9-y^2 \\
x & =\sqrt{9-y^2}
\end{aligned}
$$

This expression shows the relationship between the variables $x$ and $y$ and the constant $3$.

The expression in the image is a part of a mathematical problem involving a quadratic equation. It is written in a standard format, which can be represented in LaTeX as follows:

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{1}{2} x^2 - 1 = 0 \\
& x = \pm \sqrt{1}
\end{aligned}
$$

This expression represents the solutions to the quadratic equation $1/2 x^2 - 1 = 0$, which are $x = \pm \sqrt{1}$.
